      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "The carbocation electrophile in a Friedel–Crafts reaction can be generated by an alternate means than reaction of an alkyl chloride with AlCl<sub>3</sub>. For example, reaction of benzene with 2-methylpropene in the presence of H<sub>3</sub>PO<sub>4</sub> yields <i>tert</i>-butylbenzene. Propose a mechanism for this reaction.",
